quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  12,7,In Joseph and his brethren were signs for those who ask questions
  12,8,"When they said, 'Surely Joseph and his brother are dearer to our father than we, though we are a band. Surely our father is in manifest error"
  12,9,"Kill you Joseph, or cast him forth into some land, that your father's face may be free for you, and thereafter you may be a righteous people"
  12,10,"One of them said, 'No, kill not Joseph, but cast him into the bottom of the pit and some traveller will pick him out, if you do aught"
  12,11,"They said, 'Father, what ails thee, that thou trustest us not with Joseph? Surely we are his sincere well-wishers"
  12,12,"Send him forth with us tomorrow, to frolic and play; surely we shall be watching over him"
  12,13,"He said, 'It grieves me that you should go with him, and I fear the wolf may eat him, while you are heedless of him"
  12,14,"They said, 'If the wolf eats him, and we a band, then are we losers"
  12,15,"So when they went with him, and agreed to put him in the bottom of the well, and We revealed to him, 'Thou shalt tell them of this their doing when they are unaware"
  12,16,"And they came to their father in the evening, and they were weeping"
  12,17,"They said, 'Father, we went running races, and left Joseph behind with our things; so the wolf ate him. But thou wouldst never believe us, though we spoke truly"
  12,18,"And they brought his shirt with false blood on it. He said, 'No; but your spirits tempted you to do somewhat. But come, sweet patience! And God's succour is ever there to seek against that you describe"
  12,19,"Then came travellers, and they sent one of them, a water-drawer, who let down his bucket. 'Good news!' he said. 'Here is a young man.' So they hid him as merchandise; but God knew what they were doing"
  12,20,"Then they sold him for a paltry price, a handful of counted dirhams; for they set small store by him"